"cold_branch_recompile_spill_corruption.mst — BUG D (JIT correctness,
 SIGSEGV/wrong-object-corruption class). See tests/repros/README.md entry 3
 for the full evidence chain (repro:threshold=1, exit 139 SIGSEGV under
 release; a debug build instead panics earlier at oops/mod.rs:53 'reserved
 tag' from memory::roots::each_code_root during a scavenge nested inside
 compiled `process:` — a GC root-scan finding a corrupted oop-map slot).

 Minimized from HandlerTask>>processWork:'s exact shape (world/bench/
 richards.mst) after the DNU #deviceInAdd: investigation: an ivar is read
 into a local ('data'), used inside a two-way branch where ONE arm is
 still cold (Untaken IC) at compile time, then the SAME local is read
 AGAIN — unconditionally — several statements later, past an intervening
 branch-with-early-return. `go` runs 50000 calls exercising only the WARM
 arm first (forcing threshold=1 to compile, trap, and recompile against
 that one-sided feedback), THEN 50000 calls exercising the SIBLING arm for
 the first time ever — reproduces reliably on the very first such call.

 Interpreted (MACVM_JIT unset, or =off): completes cleanly, answers 577783.
 MACVM_JIT=threshold=1: SIGSEGV (release) / reserved-tag panic (debug),
 always on the first kind=2 call, never during the first (kind=1-only)
 loop and never if kind is interleaved from the very first call (see
 README) — the recompile-after-a-cold-sibling-branch transition is
 necessary to reproduce, not the branch shape alone."

Object subclass: Box [
    | payload other |
    payload: x [ payload := x ]
    other: x [ other := x ]
    add1: x [ payload := payload + x. ^self ]
    add2: x [ payload := payload + (x * 2). ^self ]
    payload [ ^payload ]
    other [ ^other ]
]

Object subclass: R3 [
    | handle sched |
    handle: x [ handle := x ]
    sched: x [ sched := x ]

    "Mirrors HandlerTask>>processWork:'s exact shape: an ivar-read into a
     temp near the top, an unrelated arg-only test, a two-way branch where
     each arm re-reads that SAME temp and sends it a DIFFERENT selector
     (one warm, one cold), then the temp is read AGAIN — unconditionally —
     past a further branch with an early return."
    process: kind [
        | data workPacket count devicePacket |
        data := handle.
        kind = 1
            ifTrue: [ data add1: 5 ]
            ifFalse: [ data add2: 7 ].
        workPacket := data payload.
        workPacket = 0 ifTrue: [ ^sched markWaiting ].
        count := workPacket.
        count > 1000000 ifTrue: [
            data other: workPacket.
            ^sched queuePacket: data ].
        devicePacket := count + 1.
        data other: devicePacket.
        ^sched queuePacket: data
    ]

    R3 class >> go [
        | r b s total |
        r := R3 new.
        b := Box new.
        b payload: 1.
        s := R3 new.
        r handle: b.
        r sched: s.
        total := 0.
        "First 50000 calls: kind=1 only -- the OTHER arm (kind=2) stays
         cold long enough for threshold=1 to compile, trap, and recompile
         against feedback that has STILL never seen kind=2 even once."
        1 to: 50000 do: [:i | total := total + (r process: 1) size ].
        "Now finally take the cold arm, for the very first time ever."
        1 to: 50000 do: [:i | total := total + (r process: 2) size ].
        ^total
    ]

    markWaiting [ ^'w' ]
    queuePacket: aBox [ ^aBox payload printString ]
]

Transcript show: R3 go printString; cr.
